&#xd;
At national level, FSG takes part in the following consultative bodies:&#xd;
-State Council of Social Action NGOs (Spanish Ministry of Health and Social Affairs) &#xd;
-State Council for the Roma People (Spanish Ministry of Health and Social Affairs) &#xd;
-Council for the eradication of Discrimination on Grounds of Race or Ethnicity&#xd;
&#xd;
The FSG is actively involved in several Spanish networks and alliances: &#xd;
-Spanish Platform of Social NGOs (POAS)&#xd;
-Spanish Platform of the Third Sector (PTS)&#xd;
-European Anti-Poverty Network in Spain (EAPN-ES)&#xd;
-Spanish Association of Foundations&#xd;
-Spanish Association of Fundraising&#xd;
-Platform for the Management of Diversity by Police Forces&#xd;
Lealtad Foundation (on Transparency)&#xd;
-Platform DESC a platform of NGOs that monitors the implementation of the International Covenant on Economic, Social and Cultural rights &#xd;
-Institute for the Quality of NGOs (ICONG)&#xd;
-The informal but highly consolidated network created by the FSG with the other social organisations of the ESF Operational Programme Fight Against Discrimination and the Operational Programme Social Inclusion and Social Economy (Cáritas, Cruz Roja española and Fundación Once).&#xd;
-Social Inclusion Network of Spain&#xd;
-Network for the Fight against Early School Leaving and Training&#xd;
-Forum of Society on Drugs (National Plan on Drugs, Spanish Ministry of Health, Social Services and Equality)&#xd;
-Healthy Leisure Group (National Plan on Drugs)&#xd;
-Youth Council of Spain

